[Another week's surveillance information, and the situation remains somewhat the same: continued transmission of cVDPVs (circulating vaccine-derived polioviruses) in multiple countries (Nigeria, Niger, Somalia, and Papua New Guinea), and while no new WPV1 (wild poliovirus type 1) have been officially confirmed (see section [1] above for a Pashto media report announcing a newly confirmed case of WPV1 in Helmand Province), there were 10 environmental samples taken during the month of September in Pakistan that were positive for the WPV1. Hence, the absence of officially reported/confirmed cases does not signal interruption of transmission in either Pakistan or Afghanistan.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. - Mod.MPP

